# Backend Conventions

Stack: FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, Pydantic, fastapi-users (JWT), ARQ, pgvector.

## Layer responsibilities

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `api/` | Route handlers — thin, delegate to services |
| `schemas/` | Pydantic request/response models |
| `models/` | SQLAlchemy ORM models |
| `services/` | Business logic, AI calls, ingestion |
| `db/` | Engine, session, base declarative class |
| `core/` | Settings, auth deps, shared config |

## Patterns

```python
# ✅ Route delegates to service
@router.post("/ai/score-job")
async def score_job(body: ScoreJobRequest, svc: AIService = Depends()):
    return await svc.score_job(body.job_id)

# ✅ Settings from env via pydantic-settings
class Settings(BaseSettings):
    database_url: str
    redis_url: str
    model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=".env")
```

- Use async where libraries support it (ARQ, httpx)
- Store AI outputs and generated content in PostgreSQL
- Ingestion sources implement a common interface in `services/ingestion/`
- Never commit `.env`; use `.env.example` as the template
